Russia RTS Stock-Index Futures Fall at Start of Trading

-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 
2011-04-13T15:38:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/russia-rts-stock-index-futures-fall-at-start-of-trading.html
Russia ’s RTS stock-index futures
expiring in June fell 0.2 percent to 201,000 by 11:30 a.m. in
 New York .  Contracts on OAO Lukoil, the country’s second-biggest oil
producer, dropped 0.2 percent, while contracts on OAO Sberbank,
Russia’s largest lender, declined 0.1 percent. OAO Gazprom, the
natural-gas export monopoly, slipped 0.1 percent. The Market
Vectors Russia ETF, a U.S.-traded fund that holds Russian
shares, gained almost 1 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Halia Pavliva in New York at 
 hpavliva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
